        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-23 04:17:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Why available-capacity a string, from the description of this property it is numeric value?\n> \n> Also, p-interface -> service-instance edge is redundant, we already have pnf -> service-instance, we can traverse from p-interface -> pnf (parent) -> service-instance.\n\n\n1. The available-capacity is modeled as string in line with existing implementations for attributes like speed-value, since this is also a bandwidth related attribute like speed.\n\n2. For our usecase, there are multiple p-interfaces for a particular pnf any of which can be used for a service, and there is a possibility of multiple services between the same set of p-interfaces (for example, multiple 10Gbps services on a 100Gbps p-interface). So we thought it would be appropriate to have a new relationship between service-instance and p-interface.\n\nPlease let me know if these reasons are acceptable, if not, I will make changes as per your comments.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
